import org.apache.commons.io.IOUtils
import java.net.URL
import java.nio.charset.Charset
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat
import java.util.Calendar
import java.sql.Date
import java.sql.Timestamp
var Start_Date=FileName.getTimestamp(z.input("Batch start date", "2018-09-025 00:00:00"))
var End_Date=FileName.getTimestamp(z.input("Batch end date", "2018-09-01 00:00:00"))

var result3= batch_details.toDF().sqlContext.sql(s"SELECT SUM((JOB_RUN_TIME/60)/60)AS JOB_TIMING , SUM(JOB_TOT_ENGINES)AS TOTAL_ENGINES,PZAP_APP_ID,JOB_RUN_DATE  FROM batch where SYIN_CREATE_DTM >= '$Start_Date' and SYIN_CREATE_DTM <= '$End_Date' GROUP BY PZAP_APP_ID,JOB_RUN_DATE order by JOB_RUN_DATE")
z.show(result3)
